The paper deals with the problem of parallel inference on large factor graphs, which is a common problem in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of computer clusters and distributed memory also suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). The development of a new algorithm also suggests that the paper could belong to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG).
